## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: direct|mediated — Most perception involves appresentation rather than immediate givenness; the distinction reveals hidden layers of mediation.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: perception|culture — Socio-cultural factors mediate our experience of objects and others through appresentative processes.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: sensory|interpreted — Raw sensory data transforms into interpreted meaning through appresentation.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: familiarity|recognition — Accumulated experience enriches appresentative capacity over time.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: given|constructed — Direct presentation and mediated interpretation continuously interact in perceptual experience.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: intentionality|noema — Husserl's framework of intentional directedness structures the appresentative process.

